Richie Benaud died on Friday at the age of 84  . 
  The cricket commentary box legend revealed he had skin cancer and was receiving radiation treatment . 
  He was diagnosed with skin cancers on his forehead and the top of his head last year . 
  The 84-year-old said 'as a kid we never ever wore a cap' The cricket legend said he believed the cancers were caused by playing cricket in the sun without a cap . 
  He said he was influenced by Keith Miller to not wear a cap as a child . 
  He talked about the radiation treatment he was receiving for his skin cancer . 
  Benaud was in a serious car crash in October 2013 . 
  He had not returned to his commentary job for the Nine Network . 
 